[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]Adds the decomposition element (Chaos, Life, Death, Body, Mind, Nature, etc.) to the tooltip of every researched item, so you know at a glance what an ingredient will produce at the mill, mixer, or distillation cube.[/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][b]Inline element tag[/b] on the tooltip of any item that has a decomposition target — visible in your inventory, vendor windows, chest contents, and the alchemy station inputs.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Research-gated[/b] — you only see the element on an item once you've researched it in vanilla (at the study desk, via the usual study pipeline). Unresearched items show nothing, same as vanilla. The mod never spoils anything you haven't actually unlocked.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Customisable text colour[/b] — pick any colour for the element tag via the F1 config interface. Changes apply live without restarting the game.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Localised[/b] — element names use the game's translations, so the tag reads correctly in every supported language.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Other mods of mine you might like[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/90]Alchemy Research Redux[/url] — live preview of what a combination produces at the alchemy mixer. Natural companion to Decomp Delight.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/57]Queue Everything[/url] — queue batches of decomposition / alchemy crafts. Per-workbench auto-craft covers alchemy.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/62]Where's Ma' Storage[/url] — shared inventory so the alchemy bench sees every ingredient you own.[/size]
[/list]

